reviewText: An exciting view of our young african-american youth from different backgrounds.  A study of paradoxical diversity.  I enjoyed watching.  Provide all of the seasons if possible

I wouldn't pay or suggest anyone pay full price for it, but it was pretty good for the 4.50 +shipping price. Its pretty staged like most "reality" tv, but its nice to have a show that just showed normal black teens.
